  "body": "I like to attach metadata to hardhat network config, for example:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    bsc: {\r\n      url: \"https://bsc-dataseed.binance.org/\",\r\n      accounts: [process.env.SECRET_1, process.env.SECRET_2],\r\n      swapRouter: \"0x10ED43C718714eb63d5aA57B78B54704E256024E\",\r\n      swapFactory: \"0xcA143Ce32Fe78f1f7019d7d551a6402fC5350c73\",\r\n    },\r\n    bscTestnet: {\r\n      url: \"xxx\",\r\n      accounts: [process.env.SECRET_1, process.env.SECRET_2],\r\n      swapRouter: \"0xD99D1c33F9fC3444f8101754aBC46c52416550D1\",\r\n      swapFactory: \"0x6725F303b657a9451d8BA641348b6761A6CC7a17\",\r\n    },\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis allows me to easily pass in values that belong to specific networks to particular scripts or tests.\r\n\r\nPerhaps adding a metadata field like so to make this official:\r\n\r\n```\r\nexport interface HardhatNetworkUserConfig {\r\n  chainId?: number;\r\n  from?: string;\r\n  gas?: \"auto\" | number;\r\n  gasPrice?: \"auto\" | number;\r\n  gasMultiplier?: number;\r\n  initialBaseFeePerGas?: number;\r\n  hardfork?: string;\r\n  mining?: HardhatNetworkMiningUserConfig;\r\n  accounts?: HardhatNetworkAccountsUserConfig;\r\n  blockGasLimit?: number;\r\n  minGasPrice?: number | string;\r\n  throwOnTransactionFailures?: boolean;\r\n  throwOnCallFailures?: boolean;\r\n  allowUnlimitedContractSize?: boolean;\r\n  initialDate?: string;\r\n  loggingEnabled?: boolean;\r\n  forking?: HardhatNetworkForkingUserConfig;\r\n  coinbase?: string;\r\n  metadata?: any;\r\n}\r\n```",
