    "body": "Sounds good. Especially when you have big configs, you would just assign such config file to this field.\r\n\r\nThough you already can have custom fields and get them like this `hre.network.config.metadata` where metadata is your custom field name. \r\n\r\nI wonder if it's possible to have this metadata field on Hardhat Network correspond to the current fork URL without writing my own utility scripts for this. One solution is to just allow multiple Hardhat Network entries, for example, if an entry has `forking` property set, we treat this network as Hardhat with forking.",
